----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomNavPaneToolPanel.DrawPartialMenuFrame
Summary
  Specifies how the dropdown button is drawn.
Description
  DrawPartialMenuFrame determines how the <LINK DropDownMenu> button is drawn when the drop down is
  displayed. When DrawPartialMenuFrame is true, only the top,left and right edge of the button is
  drawn. When DrawPartialMenuFrame is false, all four edges are drawn. If you are using an XP style
  menu component (like <LINK TJvPopupMenu>), you might want to set this property to true to make it
  appear as if the button and menu is a single control.
See Also
  TJvCustomNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu
Summary
  Specifies the menu to display when the user clicks the dropdown button.
Description
  Assign a TPopupMenu to the DropDownMenu property to show a menu button on the panel (at the top of
  the control) that, when clicked by the user, shows the menu. If no menu is assigned, the menu button
  is hidden.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomNavPaneToolPanel.EdgeRounding
Summary
  Specifies the rounding of various edges.
Description
