@@TJvCustomNavPaneToolPanel.GetHitTestInfoAt
Summary
  Returns information about the location of a point relative to the client area of the control.
Description
  Call GetHitTestInfoAt to determine what portion of the control, if any, sits under the point
  specified by the X and Y parameters. For example, use GetHitTestInfoAt to provide feedback about
  whether the panel can be drag and docked or not when the mouse is over the relevant portions of the
  control.
Parameters
  X - Horizontal location of mouse in client coordinates.
  Y - Vertical location of mouse in client coordinates.
Return value
  GetHitTestInfoAt returns a TJvToolPanelHitTestInfos. This set describes the possible elements under
  the mouse.
See Also
  TJvToolPanelHitTestInfo, TJvToolPanelHitTestInfos

