  * One or more tool buttons (the Buttons property)
  * An area where to display additional controls.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Background
Summary
  Manages the properties of the background image of the control.
Description
  Use the properties of Background to set and modify the background image shown in the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ButtonHeight
Summary
  Sets the height of the buttons in the toolbar.
Description
  Use ButtonHeight to specify the height of the toolbar buttons.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Buttons, TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ButtonWidth

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Buttons
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the buttons in the toolbar.
Description
  Use Buttons to access the buttons on the toolbar.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.CloseButton, TJvNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ButtonWidth
Summary
  Sets the width of the buttons in the toolbar.
Description
  Use ButtonWidth to specify the width of the toolbar buttons.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ButtonHeight, TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Buttons

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.CloseButton
Summary
  Specifies whether a close button is shown in the caption are or not.
Description
  Set CloseButton to true to display a close button in the caption area of the tool panel. If
  CloseButton is true and the user clicks on it, the OnCLose event is triggered.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu, TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnClose

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.DrawPartialMenuFrame
Summary
  Specifies how to draw the drop-down menu button.
Description
  Use DrawPartialMenuFrame to specify how the drop-down button is drawn when the drop-down menu is
  displayed. If DrawPartialMenuFrame is true, the bottom line of the frame is not drawn when the
  drop-down is visible. If DrawPartialMenuFrame is false, the bottom ine of the frame is always drawn.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.DropDownMenu
Summary
  Specifies the popup menu to show when the user clicks on the dropdown button.
Description
  Assign a TPopupMenu to this property to display a dropdown button in the caption area of the panel.
  When the user clicks the button, the popup menu is displayed below the button. If no popup menu is
  assigned, the dropdown button is hidden.
Note
  To display the dropdown button without displaying the popup menu, assign a TPopupMenu to the property
  and handle the OnDropDownMenu event. You should set Handled to true to supress the display of the
  default menu.

  You can adjust the location of the menu with the TPopupMenu.Alignment property.
See Also
  TPopupMenu

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.HeaderHeight
Summary
  Specifies the height of the caption area of the panel.
Description
  Use HeaderHeight to specify the height, in pixels, of the caption area.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Images
Summary
  Specifies the images used for the button images in the toolbar.
Description
  Assign a TCustomImageList or descendant to this property to specify the images used by the buttons on
  the toolbar of the panel. Each button aos has an ImageIndex property that specifies which image in
  Images to display for that button.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.Buttons

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnButtonClick
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks one of the buttons in the toolbar.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to take appropriate action when the user clicks one of thebuttons in
  the toolbar. This event isnot triggered when the user clicks the dropdown button or the close
  button.
Parameters
  Sender - The control that triggered the event
  Index  - The index of te clicked button in the Buttons array
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnClose, TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnDropDownMenu

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnClose
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks the close button.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to take specific action whwen the user clicks the close button. For
  example, hide the tool panel when this happens.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.CloseButton

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.OnDropDownMenu
Summary
  Occurs when the drop down menu is about to be displayed.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to take specific action when the drop down menu of the control is
  about to be displayed. For example, you can use this event to display another dialog or form instead
  of the assigned DropDownMenu. Set Handled to true to suppress the default menu.
See Also
  OnContextPopup

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ParentStyleManager
Summary
  Determines where a control looks for its style information.
Description
  To have a control use the same StyleManager as its parent control, set ParentStyleManager to true. If
  ParentStyleManager is false, the control does not change its StyleManager property to match that of
  its parent.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.StyleManager

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ShowGrabber
Summary
  Specifies whether grab handles are displayed in the caption.
Description
  Use ShowGrabber to specify whether a grab handle" (a row of vertical dots) are displayed at the left
  edge of the control. The grabber is normally used to indicate that the panel can be undocked from the
  form it is placed on but can also be used for other purposes (for example, to indicate and initiate
  resizing).
Note
  The panel does not have any built in docking or sizing support. You will have to implement this
  yourself. For an example on how this could be done, see the demo.
See Also
  GetHitTestInfoAt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavPaneToolPanel.StyleManager
Summary
  Specifies the component responsible for handling the control's styles.
Description
  Assign a style manager to this property to make the style manager handle the control's theme
  settings. When the Theme property of the style manager changes, the corresponding properties in the
  control changes as well.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneToolPanel.ParentStyleManager

