@@TJvOutlookSplitter
<TITLEIMG TJvOutlookSplitter>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.FormsAndApp.Forms.Sizing
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A splitter drawn in the style of the splitter used in Outlook 2003.
Description
  TJvOutlookSplitter is a normal splitter with additional properties and events to make it appear
  visually like the splitter introduced in Outlook 2003.
Note
  The Color property is not used by TJvOutlookSplitter. TSplitter publishes the Color property and
  TJvOutlookSplitter inherits it. To modify the colors of a TJvOutlookSplitter, use ColorFrom and
  ColorTo instead.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.ColorFrom
Summary
  Specifies the starting color of the control's background gradient.
Description
  Use ColorFrom to specify the starting color of the gradient drawn on the control.
See Also
  TJvOutlookSplitter.ColorTo

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.ColorTo
Summary
  Specifies the ending color of the control's background gradient.
Description
  Use ColorFrom to specify the starting color of the gradient drawn on the control.
See Also
  TJvOutlookSplitter.ColorFrom

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.Cursor
Summary
  Specifies the mouse cursor to display when the mouse is moved over the control.
Description
  Use Cursor to set the mouse cursor to display when the mouse is over the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.DragZone
Summary
  Specifies the area where dragging is allowed.
Description
  DragZone is the number of pixels in the center of the control that constitutes the draggable area.
  For example, with a left/right aligned splitter and a DragZone of 100, 50 pixels above and 50 pixels
  below the vertical midpoint can be clicked to start the sizing. Any clicks outside this area will not
  start a sizing operation. If DragZone <= 0, the entire control is a drag zone

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.ParentStyleManager
Summary
  Determines where a control looks for its style information.
Description
  To have a control use the same StyleManager as its parent control, set ParentStyleManager to true. If
  ParentStyleManager is false, the control does not change its StyleManager property to match that of
  its parent.
See Also
  TJvOutlookSplitter.StyleManager

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvOutlookSplitter.StyleManager
Summary
  Specifies the component responsible for handling the control's styles.
Description
  Assign a style manager to this property to make the style manager handle the control's theme
  settings. When the Theme property of the style manager changes, the corresponding properties in the
  control changes as well.
See Also
  TJvOutlookSplitter.ParentStyleManager

